/mol [CI, 1.64 to 8.61]; P&#x0200a;=&#x0200a;0.005) and insulin glargine plus glimepirde (0.59% [CI, 0.13% to 1.05%]; P&#x0200a;=&#x0200a;0.012) (5.87 mmol/mol [CI, 1.10 to 10.64]; P&#x0200a;=&#x0200a;0.012) (overall P&#x0200a;=&#x0200a;0.02) (<xref ref-type="table" rid="pone-0087799-t002">Table 2</xref>). The participants measured by HbA1C level less than 6.5% over the study duration did not differ among the groups. However, more patients reached an HbA1c level of 7.5% or less with insulin glargine plus glimepirde plus metformin (24 of 32 [75.0%]) than with insulin glargine plus metformin (14 of 33 [43.8%]; <italic>P</italic>&#x0200a;=&#x0200a;0.0109) (<xref ref-type="table" rid="pone-0087799-t002">Table 2</xref>).</p><fig id="pone-0087799-g002" orientation="portrait" position="float"><object-id pub-id-type="doi">10.1371/journal.pone.0087799.g002</object-id><label>Figure 2</label><caption><title>Reduction in mean HbA1C(A) and FPG(B) from Baseline to end of study.</title><p>Abbreviations are; FPG&#x0200a;=&#x0200a;Fasting plasma glucose.</p></caption><graphic xlink:href="pone.0087799.g002"/></fig><table-wrap id="pone-0087799-t002" orientation="portrait" position="float"><object-id pub-id-type="doi">10.1371/journal.pone.0087799.t002</object-id><label>Table 2</label><caption><title>Effect of insulin glargin plus metformin, insulin glargin plus glimepirde or insulin glargin plus glimepirde plus metformin on Glycemic Control.</title></caption><alternatives><graphic id="pone-0087799-t002-2" xlink:href="pone.0087799.t002"/><table frame="hsides" rules="groups"><colgroup span="1"><col align="left" span="1"/><col align="center" span="1"/><col align="center" span="1"/><col align="center" span="1"/><col align="center" span="1"/></colgroup><thead><tr><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1"/><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">Insulin glargine + metformin</td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">Insulin glargine + glimepiride</td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">Insulin glargine + metformin+glimepiride</td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">Overall P value</td></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">Patients, n</td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">32</td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">32</td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">32</td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1"/></tr><tr><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">Mean improvement in HbA1c level<xref ref-type="table-fn" rid="nt105">&#x02020;</xref> (95% CI), %</td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">&#x02212;0.75 (&#x02212;1.14, &#x02212;0.36)</td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">&#x02212;0.7<xref ref-type="table-fn" rid="nt106">&#x02021;</xref> (&#x02212;1.15, &#x02212;0.26)</td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">&#x02212;1.41<xref ref-type="table-fn" rid="nt107">&#x000a7;</xref> (&#x02212;1.67, &#x02212;1.16)</td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">0.02</td></tr><tr><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">HbA1c level &#x0003c;7.0%, n (%)</td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">5(15.6)</td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">10<xref ref-type="table-fn" rid="nt108">&#x02225;</xref> (31.3)</td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">11<xref ref-type="table-fn" rid="nt109">&#x000b6;</xref> (34.4)</td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">0.1949</td></tr><tr><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">HbA1c level &#x0003c;7.5%, n (%)</td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">14(43.8)</td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">18<xref ref-type="table-fn" rid="nt110">#</xref> (56.3)</td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">24<xref ref-type="table-fn" rid="nt111">&#x000b1;</xref> (75.0)</td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">0.0385</td></tr></tbody></table></alternatives><table-wrap-foot><fn id="nt105"><label>&#x02020;</label><p>From end point to baseline.</p></fn><fn id="nt106"><label>&#x02021;</label><p>P&#x0200a;=&#x0200a;0.2 versus Insulin glargine + metformin.